# WHY these ARE tracked despite being generated: main.py's actual runtime
# code path reads these five files directly (scoring.py, embeddings.py,
# program_data.py) — they're not build-only intermediates like courses.json/
# courses_slim.json above. A deploy environment (Railway, etc.) builds from
# a fresh git clone with no access to this machine's filesystem, so if these
# aren't committed, the app either crashes on startup (courses_all_enriched.json,
# read at module import time) or crashes on first /chat request (the .npy/
# codes.json pairs). Total size is ~9.2MB — trivial for git.
# backend/course_codes.json
# backend/course_embeddings.npy
# backend/program_codes.json
# backend/program_embeddings.npy
# backend/courses_all_enriched.json

# SQLite database (chat sessions, reviews) - local dev data, not shared via git
backend/myuoft.db

# Claude Code agent scratch state (per-agent memory, not project config)
.claude/agent-memory/

# Playwright MCP output (screenshots/traces from browser-driven testing)
.playwright-mcp/